==The crackdown==
In a scandal involving a case to defraud the [[Medicaid]] and other healthcare programs such as [[Medicare (United States)|Medicare]], providing health care to senior citizens and elderly,<ref name=Herald>
{{cite news
| url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/breaking-news/dozens-arrested-in-us-medicare-scheme/story-e6frf7jx-1225938441766 |title=Dozens arrested in US Medicare scheme 
|publisher=Herald Sun 
|date=October 13, 2010 
|accessdate=October 13, 2010}}</ref> in the amounts totalling $163 million, more than 50 ethnic [[Armenians]] living in the [[United States]] were arrested on October 13, 2010. The operation was run by more than 400 [[FBI]] agents.<ref>
{{cite news
| url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2010/10/dozens-in-los-angeles-arrested-in-medicare-fraud-crackdown.html 
|title=Dozens in L.A. arrested in federal Medicare fraud crackdown 
|publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]] 
|date=October 13, 2010 
|accessdate=October 13, 2010}}</ref> In additional to FBI, [[IRS]] and local enforcement agencies in California, Georgia, New Mexico, New York and Ohio were involved in the probe.<ref>
{{cite news
| url=http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/nation/la-me-healthcare-fraud-raid-20101014,0,7387144.story
|title=52 arrested in sweeping Medicare fraud case 
|publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]]
|author=Scott Glover 
|date=October 14, 2010 
|accessdate=October 13, 2010}}</ref> The Justice Department already indicted 73 individuals in [[New York]] and four other states. 44 defendants were indicted in New York, along with 10 in California, seven in New Mexico, six in Ohio and six in Georgia.<ref name=CNN/> According to the authorities, the Armenian-American organized crime group operated across 25 states.<ref name="NPR">
{{cite news
